The colors are primarily dark blues, purples, and neon accents, emphasizing the sci-fi theme.

The animation has a clean, stylized, and slightly cinematic feel.
It seems suitable for a sci-fi intro, a game cinematic, or a mysterious space-themed scene.

On the sign up page of Lottie Finance, users are greeted by a animation that captures the essence of the appâs promise: smart banking made effortless.

At the heart of the animation is the Lottie Finance icon, reimagined as a visual thread that uses a series of meaningful metaphors. The icon travels fluidly across different metaphors, each representing a core value of the brand:

1) A secure lock â emphasizing safety and strong commitment to security.

2) A shopping cart â speed and convenience in daily transactions and spending.

3) A sailing boat â evoking the smooth, stable experience users can expect.

4) A peaceful, smiling face â ease and clarity comes with banking

Clean, minimal, and modern, the animation brings personality to the brand and sets the tone for what users can expect throughout the app: banking that feels seamless, human, and beautifully simple.

Similarly, each day includes morning sunrise, afternoon, and evening sunset. 
Each day is a new opportunity to start anew, to be present, to be mindful.
Give yourself grace and patience (especially on cloudy, rainy days).
Every effort you put forth matters (but don't forget to rest).
Focus on taking it a step at a time, a day at a time, 
Rather than the entire journey as a whole.

https://assets-v2.lottiefiles.com/a/dfc7.title: Cytokines act in 3 ways
https://assets-v2.lottiefiles.com/a/dfc7.description:
Cytokines may signal cells close to the cell that released them, or they can travel great distances to relay their message.

- Autocrine signaling: Cytokines can bind to receptors on the same cell that released it.

- Paracrine signaling: Cytokines can bind to receptors on nearby cells.

- Endocrine signaling: Cytokines can bind to receptors on cells located far away from the cell that released the cytokines. (Clevelandclinic)

Acute inflammation begins within seconds to minutes following injury to tissues. It is characterised by four cardinal features (Latin terms in brackets):

Redness (rubor) â secondary to vasodilatation and increased blood flow

Heat (calor) â localised increase in temperature, also due to increased blood flow

Swelling (tumour) â results from increased vessel permeability, allowing fluid loss into the interstitial space

Pain (dolor) â caused by stimulation of the local nerve endings, from mechanical and chemical mediators.(source: teachmesurgery.com)
